    {
        "content": "<p>It probably doesn't help here, but note that <code>{x : σ → K | ∀ i , x i ∈ A}</code> can be replaced with <code>Finset.univ.pi fun _ : σ =&gt; A</code>, which lets you define your locii as <code>Finset</code>s directly.</p>",
        "id": 573135936,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1770753038
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can use <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=finprod#doc\">docs#finprod</a> to make your product.</p>",
        "id": 573148953,
